Cell.Text: [S] I am Larak's daughter. Soon, I'll be of age and will be sent to marry an Orc chief in some distant stronghold. | Until then, I train. My new home will need strength, and my new sisters most know I am not weak when I arrive.

Node.Caption: DialogueMorKhazgurBorgakhRoleTopic: What do you do for the stronghold?

Cell.Text: No. A chief's daughter marries who her chief wishes. It ensures the stronghold receives a fair trade in goods for my absence. | I used to look forward to the day when I was of age, to see new places and people, but now it feels like a cage.

Node.Caption: DialogueMorKhazgurBorgakhMarryTopic: You don't know who you'll marry?

Cell.Text: S|Yes, but I must stay here and wait for the day when I'll be married and sent to another stronghold. | It is our way, and I am proud to follow my people's traditions, but I can't help but feel chained.
I couldn't. It would shame my chief and my mother and foremothers.

Node.Caption: DialogueMorKhazgurBorgakhLeaveTopic: You want to leave the stronghold?

Cell.Text: [S] You're right. Mauloch teaches us to meet our fate. Perhaps this is mine.
What do you know about my people, outlander?
[S] That is a fine idea. The stronghold would need the gold when I left to marry, anyway. I am ready when you are.

Node.Caption: DialogueMorKhazgurBorgakhBribe: What if I pay off your dowry? ( Gold)

Cell.Text: [S] I am not weak. Very well, outlander, I will go with you whenever you are ready.
Too weak to make your own decisions? (Brawl)
[S] G|<<Shared>> I don't have to take this from the likes of you.

Node.Caption: DialogueMorKhazgurBorgakhIntimidate: Too weak to make your own decisions? (Intimidate)
